node.text: In Analemma: Edges Without Names, Alvin Zafra plays with various registers of form. As the title alludes to graphs that track the sun’s positions from a fixed point, the artist balances the formal and the referential. Through drawing, he registers objects as geometries, turning dimension into line, duration into an instant.
